<html>
    <head>
        <title>
            Text-Shadow and Box-Shadow
        </title>
        <style>
            h1{
                text-shadow:3px 2px 0px red;
            }
            p{
                box-shadow:6px 10px 2px black;
            }
            h2{
                text-indent:40%; 
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>
            Text Shadow and Box Shadow
        </h1>
        <p>
            The CSS properties text-shadow and box-shadow are both used to add depth and visual effects, but they apply to different elements and have slightly different functionalities. The key distinction is that text-shadow is for text only, while box-shadow is for the entire element's box model. 
        </p>
        <h2>
            This is an example of text indent.
        </h2>
    </body>
</html>
